[[Niner Skirata|Niner's]] '''squad''' was a [[Squad/Legends|unit]] consisting of [[Clone commando/Legends|clone commandos]] in the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic's]] [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army]] who fought in the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] between the Galactic Republic and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]]. The unit was made up of four [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone]] [[Commando/Legends|commandos]] and led by [[Niner Skirata|Niner]], and was trained by [[Sergeant/Legends|Sergeant]] [[Kal Skirata]]. In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], the squad was deployed to the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|First Battle of Geonosis]], of which Niner was the squad's only survivor.

==History==
[[Niner Skirata|Niner's]] [[Squad/Legends|squad]] was a group of [[Clone commando/Legends|clone commandos]] who served in the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic's]] [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army]] from [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]] to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].<ref name="Dates" /> [[Cloning/Legends|Cloned]]<ref name="RC:HC" /> on the [[Wild Space/Legends|Wild Space]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> [[Kamino/Legends|Kamino]] in 32 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|BBY]],<ref name="Dates" /> the squad was led by Niner, and consisted of [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone]] [[Commando/Legends|commandos]] [[Two-Eight]], [[O-Four]], [[DD]], and [[Sev (Niner's squad)|Sev]]. During the commandos' training under ''[[Cuy'val Dar]]'' training [[Sergeant/Legends|Sergeant]] [[Kal Skirata]] on Kamino, 28 was killed due to an explosives error of his own doing on a live-range exercise&mdash;an event that would weigh heavily on the squad leader. The squad received either O-Four, DD, or Sev as a replacement in 28's stead, but Niner observed that the new trooper seemed to feel as if he was not accepted by the unit.<ref name="RC:HC" /> In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]]<ref name="Dates" /> the squad was deployed<ref name="RC:HC" /> to the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] world<ref name="TEA" /> of [[Geonosis/Legends|Geonosis]] in the first [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|battle]] of the Clone Wars. In the battle, three of the squad's members were [[Death/Legends|killed]] in action, leaving Niner as the only survivor to be assigned to [[Omega Squad]] shortly after, which he remained as squad leader for the duration of the war.<ref name="RC:HC" />

==Behind the scenes==
RC-1309's squad was mentioned in the [[2004]] novel ''[[Republic Commando: Hard Contact]]'', written by [[Karen Traviss]].<ref name="RC:HC" /> In a [[2005]] discussion forum on [[StarWars.com]], Traviss stated that RC-1309's original squad was named "Lambda Squad" in her notes for ''Hard Contact'',<ref name="SWBs">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=239051&start=15#13161930|thread=Ask Karen...(Karen Traviss approved)|user=[[Karen Traviss]]|date=2005-10-29|time=1:04 AM|quote=In my notes (and that means this isn't official, remember) Niner's old squad was Lambda, Fi's was Teroch and Atin's was Prudii.}}</ref> but the name did not appear in the novel itself.<ref name="RC:HC" />

